import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.cluster.hierarchy import dendrogram, linkage

# c d liu ca file CSV vo trong DataFrame
df = pd.read_csv("../Desktop/countries_filtered.csv")

# Gp kinh  v v  thnh ta 
coordinates = df[['latitude', 'longitude']].values

# To biu  phn tn
plt.figure(figsize=(30, 15))
plt.scatter(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=df)

# Add country labels
for i, row in df.iterrows():
    plt.annotate(row['name'], (row['longitude'], row['latitude']), textcoords="offset points", xytext=(0,10), ha='center')

plt.title('Biu  phn tn ta  cc nc chu  v u')
plt.xlabel('Kinh ')
plt.ylabel('V ')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.cluster.hierarchy import dendrogram, linkage

# c d liu ca file CSV vo trong DataFrame
df = pd.read_csv("../Desktop/countries_filtered.csv")

# Gp kinh  v v  thnh ta 
coordinates = df[['latitude', 'longitude']].values

# Thc hin phn cm phn cp
linked = linkage(coordinates, 'ward')

# V ra s  dendrogram
plt.figure(figsize=(30, 40))
dendrogram(linked,
           orientation='left',
           labels=df['name'].tolist(),
           distance_sort='descending',
           show_leaf_counts=True,
           leaf_font_size=12,
           above_threshold_color='b',
           color_threshold=80.0)
plt.title('Phn cm da theo kinh v v  ca cc nc  v u', fontsize=30)
plt.xlabel('Khong cch', fontsize=30)
plt.ylabel('Cc nc',fontsize=30)
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# c d liu t tp CSV
df = pd.read_csv('../Desktop/2021.csv')

# Loi b ct 'id' v chuyn i cc gi tr rng thnh NaN
df = df.iloc[:, 1:]

# Ly danh sch cc mn hc t tn ct
subjects = df.columns

# Tnh im trung bnh ca tng mn hc
avg_scores = df.mean()

# V biu  ct
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
bars = plt.bar(subjects, avg_scores, color='skyblue')
plt.title('Biu  im Trung Bnh Cc Mn Hc')
plt.xlabel('Mn Hc')
plt.ylabel('im Trung Bnh')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Hin th im trung bnh  u mi ct
for bar, avg_score in zip(bars, avg_scores):
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, avg_score, f'{avg_score:.2f}', ha='center', va='bottom')

plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# c d liu t tp CSV
df = pd.read_csv('../Desktop/2021.csv')

# Loi b ct 'id' v chuyn i cc gi tr rng thnh NaN
df = df.iloc[:, 1:]
df = df.notnull().astype('int')  # Chuyn cc gi tr thnh 0 (nu rng) hoc 1 (nu c gi tr)

# Ly danh sch cc mn hc t tn ct
subjects = df.columns

# Tnh tng s th sinh thi tng mn hc
total_students = df.sum()

# V biu  ct
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.bar(subjects, total_students, color='skyblue')
plt.title('S Lng Th Sinh Thi Tng Mn Hc')
plt.xlabel('Mn Hc')
plt.ylabel('S Lng Th Sinh')

# Hin th s th sinh  u mi ct
for i, v in enumerate(total_students):
    plt.text(i, v, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom')

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from scipy.cluster.hierarchy import linkage, dendrogram
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# c d liu t tp CSV hoc ngun d liu khc
df = pd.read_csv('../Desktop/2021.csv')

# in gi tr NaN bng 0
df = df.fillna(0)

# Ly cc ct cha im s (loi b ct 'id')
X = df.iloc[:, 1:]
# print(X)

# Ly tn cc mn hc
subject_names = X.columns.tolist()
# print(subject_names)

# Chuyn DataFrame thnh mng NumPy v chuyn v ma trn (transpose)
X = X.values.T
# print(X)

# Tnh ma trn lin kt
linkage_matrix = linkage(X, method='ward')

# V dendrogram vi tn mn hc
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
dendrogram(linkage_matrix, labels=subject_names)
plt.xlabel('Mn hc')
plt.ylabel('Khong cch')
plt.title('Phn cm phn cp theo im mn hc')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)  # Xoay tn mn hc  hin th d c
plt.show()
